      "id": "inv-001",
      "topic": "Inventory",
      "subtopic": "Lower of Cost or Net Realizable Value",
      "stem": "Under ASC 330, inventory should be measured at:",
      "choices": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "Lower of cost or market (replacement cost)"
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "Lower of cost or net realizable value"
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "Fair value"
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "Historical cost without adjustment"
        }
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "B",
      "explanation": "ASU 2015-11 simplified the measurement of inventory by requiring entities that use FIFO or average cost to measure inventory at the lower of cost or net realizable value (NRV). NRV is estimated selling price less reasonably predictable costs of completion, disposal, and transportation. The previous lower of cost or market (with ceiling and floor tests) was eliminated for non-LIFO methods.",
      "explanationJa": "ASU 2015-11により、FIFOまたは平均原価法を使用する企業は棚卸資産を原価とNRVのいずれか低い方で測定する。NRV = 見積売価 - 完成・処分・輸送の合理的見積費用。非LIFO法では従前のLCM（上限・下限テスト）は廃止された。",
      "references": [
        "ASC 330-10-35-1B"
      ],
      "difficulty": "basic",
      "source": "AICPA Released Questions"
    },
